cate an infection, inflammation, or a underlying condition affecting the immune system.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046933,0.079176,0.098651,0.11526,0.10749,0.10248,0.10133,0.090352,0.080331,0.074963,0.057665,0.045372],"unified_progress":[0.044094,0.077956,0.099175,0.10933,0.10511,0.10457,0.10113,0.092961,0.08535,0.077413,0.060576,0.042329]},{"section":6,"text":"The histopathological examination of the enlarged lymph node showed something interesting: the architecture was effaced by a diffuse proliferation of small, mature-looking lymphoid cells.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031624,0.067212,0.092785,0.1136,0.11873,0.11871,0.11553,0.101,0.080943,0.06451,0.053198,0.042149],"unified_progress":[0.03509,0.075175,0.09643,0.10873,0.11452,0.1071,0.10138,0.093281,0.091982,0.071555,0.05807,0.046685]},{"section":7,"text":"Effaced architecture usually means that the normal structure of the lymph node is being replaced, which is a sign of something abnormal.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044226,0.05744,0.075933,0.089975,0.10218,0.10798,0.10939,0.10564,0.097049,0.083184,0.068521,0.058479],"unified_progress":[0.041005,0.063465,0.082074,0.095056,0.099984,0.11702,0.10426,0.098123,0.092149,0.083914,0.068744,0.054202]},{"section":8,"text":"The cells are small and mature, which makes me think of B-cells because B-cells can sometimes form these types of proliferations.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038725,0.056335,0.073325,0.085795,0.097361,0.10321,0.10642,0.10545,0.10062,0.090648,0.07622,0.065883],"unified_progress":[0.036475,0.061284,0.081236,0.09382,0.099498,0.1071,0.10467,0.10061,0.095255,0.089028,0.073381,0.057643]},{"section":9,"text":"Looking at the peripheral blood results, there's lymphocytosis, which means an increase in white blood cells, specifically lymphocytes.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035294,0.067622,0.091842,0.1043,0.11258,0.1118,0.10941,0.093955,0.083792,0.072551,0.06351,0.053342],"unified_progress":[0.041377,0.076219,0.092013,0.099747,0.10516,0.10153,0.1008,0.093619,0.089231,0.078719,0.068214,0.053362]},{"section":10,"text":"Additionally, the blood test showed CD5-positive and CD23-positive B-cells.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032035,0.064302,0.089841,0.10764,0.11578,0.11755,0.11724,0.098888,0.083055,0.068041,0.057792,0.047844],"unified_progress":[0.037819,0.074284,0.092323,0.10398,0.10892,0.10388,0.10468,0.09225,0.091765,0.074509,0.063404,0.052181]},{"section":11,"text":"CD5 is a marker expressed on B-cells, especially in chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL), and CD23 is also a B-cell marker.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026788,0.050266,0.072181,0.086537,0.10457,0.11262,0.11468,0.11298,0.10514,0.08715,0.068602,0.058489],"unified_progress":[0.030631,0.059571,0.081995,0.095968,0.10155,0.12524,0.10859,0.10134,0.092933,0.084912,0.067268,0.050007]},{"section":12,"text":"The presence of these markers suggests that the B-cells are the ones that are overactive or in an abnormal state.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042569,0.055281,0.072739,0.084407,0.094981,0.10042,0.10362,0.10124,0.097498,0.090525,0.081236,0.07549],"unified_progress":[0.043808,0.064395,0.078756,0.089107,0.095399,0.10036,0.09955,0.098142,0.094391,0.088379,0.079374,0.068342]},{"section":13,"text":"Putting this together, the patient has generalized weakness, which could be due to an underlying systemic issue, and the lymphadenopathy along with the histopathology and blood findings point towards a B-cell disorder.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035084,0.050314,0.059627,0.067138,0.069155,0.073236,0.078611,0.084371,0.090498,0.10468,0.12179,0.1655],"unified_progress":[0.033819,0.050272,0.058356,0.066957,0.070707,0.078994,0.081626,0.090732,0.0